name: Anchors Aweigh
comments: Originally written as a class song for the US Naval Academy. It has gone through several revisions over the years. See the comments for each version to determine which one to apply any vocal performances to. The original lyrics do not include the "Anchors aweigh, my boys" verse (which was added in 1926). The current lyrics were published in 1997.

name: Anchors Aweigh
comments: Full lyrics of the third verse: Blue of the Seven Seas; Gold of God's great sun Let these our colors be Till All of time be done-n-n-ne, By Severn shore we learn Navy's stern call: Faith, courage, service true With honor over, honor over all.
adapted_from:
Anchors Aweigh written by Alfred H. Miles , Charles A. Zimmermann -
                            3rd verse added ("Blue of the Seven Seas / Gold of God's great sun ...")

name: Anchors Aweigh
comments: First two verses of this version: 1. Stand, Navy, out to sea, Fight our battle cry; We'll never change our course, So vicious foe steer shy-y-y-y. Roll out the TNT, Anchors Aweigh. Sail on to victory And sink their bones To Davy Jones, hooray! 2. Anchors Aweigh, my boys, Anchors Aweigh. Farewell to college joys, We sail at break of day-ay-ay-ay. Through our last night on shore, Drink to the foam, Until we meet once more. Here's wishing you a happy voyage home.
adapted_from:
Anchors Aweigh written by Alfred H. Miles , Charles A. Zimmermann -
                            First verse rewritten (now beginning "Stand Navy, out to sea" instead of the original "Stand, Navy, down the field") and a new second verse (beginning "Anchors aweigh, my boys") was added. This version was published after the third verse was added by Royal Lovell

comments: Lyrics for this version from the USNA website: Verse 1 Stand Navy out to sea, Fight our battle cry; We'll never change our course, So vicious foe steer shy-y-y-y.
